<TITLE> President, PM pay tribute to language heroes </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 21 (bdnews24.com)  The nation was paying tribute to the martyred heroes of the 1952 Bangla Language Movement from the first minutes of Sunday, being observed round the world too as International Mother Language Day. Thousands of people had flocked towards the Central Shaheed Minar ahead of midnight, when as is tradition the first of a sea of floral tributes are laid down at the monument by national leaders, led by the president. President Mohammad Zillur Rahman laid the first tribute down, minutes after zero hour, a circular wreath of green and red with a Shapla flower at the centre. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina followed with a similar one. b
